ch, or maybe it's something that's been recent.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052395,0.081763,0.092214,0.09332,0.093567,0.093983,0.094083,0.091935,0.088657,0.086254,0.07542,0.05641],"unified_progress":[0.063393,0.085545,0.08647,0.088423,0.092039,0.09302,0.092882,0.094695,0.090107,0.087417,0.073359,0.05265]},{"section":11,"text":"Visual acuity is diminished in both eyes, so his vision is poor in both eyes.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052053,0.073488,0.09058,0.099988,0.10379,0.10382,0.10159,0.093643,0.084688,0.07514,0.066016,0.055211],"unified_progress":[0.05418,0.078402,0.090421,0.09654,0.10044,0.099032,0.096502,0.092064,0.091106,0.079174,0.068087,0.054047]},{"section":12,"text":"That points towards a binocular vision issue, but more specifically, it's likely affecting both eyes in a similar way.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049463,0.065515,0.083131,0.095397,0.098592,0.099837,0.10114,0.095616,0.088995,0.085541,0.073294,0.063477],"unified_progress":[0.045454,0.069568,0.085673,0.095981,0.098943,0.098995,0.099182,0.095578,0.092025,0.085744,0.07353,0.059326]},{"section":13,"text":"Visual charting showed a significant field defect.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033058,0.065708,0.089515,0.10964,0.11348,0.11519,0.11341,0.10143,0.084071,0.06887,0.058365,0.047267],"unified_progress":[0.036771,0.074201,0.094011,0.10656,0.11052,0.10491,0.10069,0.093099,0.092271,0.074506,0.061535,0.05092]},{"section":14,"text":"Visual field defects can be a sign of various conditions.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039383,0.063364,0.082167,0.097734,0.10207,0.1038,0.10825,0.099619,0.091264,0.085964,0.069406,0.056987],"unified_progress":[0.039025,0.069121,0.087246,0.09917,0.10199,0.10549,0.10405,0.097719,0.091618,0.084334,0.06859,0.051653]},{"section":15,"text":"For example, if the field defect is in both eyes, it could be something like a chiasmic defect, which is common in conditions like optic neuritis or optic atrophy.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032431,0.052942,0.073985,0.089189,0.099982,0.10578,0.11006,0.10805,0.10195,0.093963,0.072971,0.0587],"unified_progress":[0.03372,0.063026,0.085022,0.097541,0.1025,0.10836,0.10687,0.10229,0.09552,0.087638,0.068869,0.048643]},{"section":16,"text":"But the CT scan result is important here.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039508,0.066327,0.080652,0.091778,0.09628,0.099263,0.10167,0.098381,0.092977,0.089591,0.080644,0.06293],"unified_progress":[0.037796,0.068021,0.083415,0.094436,0.10023,0.09842,0.098611,0.097622,0.095362,0.091044,0.075793,0.059252]},{"section":17,"text":"The CT scan showed a suprasellar mass with calcification.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02537,0.059091,0.088082,0.11791,0.11888,0.12191,0.11934,0.10595,0.08493,0.065057,0.052674,0.040799],"unified_progress":[0.031725,0.072223,0.094558,0.113,0.11383,0.10695,0.10281,0.093286,0.095936,0.071368,0.057104,0.047215]},{"section":18,"text":"The supraseller area is the region above the sella turcica, which is where the optic chiasm is located.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033275,0.057674,0.078674,0.093801,0.10736,0.11341,0.11404,0.10914,0.097722,0.080399,0.063376,0.051128],"unified_progress":[0.03581,0.065785,0.0856,0.099989,0.10434,0.12219,0.10575,0.097417,0.091698,0.079942,0.06276,0.048714]},{"section":19,"text":"Calcification in this area could indicate a tumor, maybe a craniopharyngeal ganglioglioma or a calcified pituitary adenoma, but more likely, given the age and the location, it's a tumor affecting the optic chiasm.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033383,0.054682,0.076308,0.091268,0.10021,0.10522,0.10901,0.10564,0.098123,0.090565,0.074181,0.06141],"unified_progress":[0.037464,0.066718,0